                "href": "/profile/Satya-Amar-2"
            },
            "answer_text": "I observed that 12xy is symmetric with respect to x and y but neither (x+3y) nor (x-3y) is symmetric with respect to x and y. So I started to combine both the parameters to make a symmetric function. But suddenly I saw the coefficient 12(which is 4*3) and the result (a+b)^2-(a-b)^2=4ab stroke into my mind. So I calculated (x+ 3y)^2-(x- 3y)^2 which simplifies to 12xy. O yeah! I got it! Hence f(x+3y,x-3y)=(x+3y)^2- (x- 3y)^2. Therefore f(x,y)=x^2-y^2. Hope this small journey is useful for you. ",
