            "answer_text": "Suppose x+3y=p,x\u22123y=qx+3y=p,x\u22123y=q So we get, x=p+q2x=p+q2 y=p\u2212q6y=p\u2212q6 Putting these equations in the function definition, f(p,q)=12p+q2p\u2212q6f(p,q)=12p+q2p\u2212q6 \u2234f(p,q)=(p+q)(p\u2212q)\u2234f(p,q)=(p+q)(p\u2212q) Now you can use any variable as parameter. Hence the required answer is, f(x,y)=(x+y)(x\u2212y)=x2\u2212y2f(x,y)=(x+y)(x\u2212y)=x2\u2212y2 Hope it helps! ",
